  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Data Center Engineer L1",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform daily operational tasks in the data center, including system monitoring, hardware checks, and facility inspections.</li>\n  <li>Provide first-level support for IT infrastructure issues (e.g., servers, storage, network equipment).</li>\n  <li>Perform routine tasks such as racking/stacking of hardware, cable patching, and physical inventory checks.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with vendors for hardware installation, maintenance, and troubleshooting.</li>\n  <li>Ensure proper documentation of assets and update logs or systems accurately.</li>\n  <li>Maintain a clean, organized, and secure data center environment.</li>\n  <li>Respond to incidents according to defined SLA and escalate issues when necessary.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma or Nitec in Information Technology, Engineering, or related field.</li>\n  <li>0–2 years of experience in IT infrastructure or data center operations.</li>\n  <li>Basic understanding of server hardware, cabling, and networking.</li>\n  <li>Physically fit to handle equipment and work in a cold environment.</li>\n  <li>Good communication skills and a team player.</li>\n  <li>Entry-level candidates are welcome to apply; training will be provided.</li>\n</ul>",
